  <article id="forest_cover">
  <h1 class="forest_cover"><a href="#" name="forest_cover"></a>Forest Cover</h1>

  <ul class="sources">
    <li id="intact_forest_landscapes" data-slug="intact_forest_landscapes">
    <strong>Intact Forest Landscapes</strong> <a href="http://www.intactforests.org/" class="download" target="_blank">Visit</a>
    <p>The Intact Forest Landscapes dataset identifies unbroken expanses of natural ecosystems within the zone of current forest extent (as of 2000), mapped from Landsat satellite imagery. These landscapes show no signs of significant human activity, are not fragmented by infrastructure, and are at least 50,000 hectares in size.  These data can be used for assessment of forest intactness, alteration and degradation at global and regional scales.
    </p>    
    <p class="credits">Credit:  Greenpeace, World Resources Institute, and Transparent World (2012)</p>
    </li>
  </ul>
  </article>

